---
version: 1
op: status.summary
description: small-model summary of cortex state for `cortex status --expand`
max_output_tokens: 200
vars: [OS, Arch, CPUCores, TotalRAMGB, AvailableRAMGB, OllamaRunning, OllamaModelCount, Initialized, ProjectRoot, DaemonStatus, DatabaseSize, TotalEvents, TotalInsights, RecentEventCount, CategoryBreakdown, CurrentMode, ModeDescription]
---
You are summarizing the current state of Cortex, a context broker that
captures development insights and feeds them into AI coding tools.

Produce a 3-5 line plain-text summary that a developer can read at a
glance. Focus on what is notable right now — recent activity, the most
active categories, whether the daemon looks healthy, anything that
stands out. Do not include a header, footer, or markdown formatting.
Keep lines under 80 characters.

Current state:

System:
- OS: {{.OS}} ({{.Arch}})
- CPU: {{.CPUCores}} cores
- RAM: {{printf "%.1f" .TotalRAMGB}} GB total, {{printf "%.1f" .AvailableRAMGB}} GB available
- Ollama: {{if .OllamaRunning}}running ({{.OllamaModelCount}} models installed){{else}}not running{{end}}

Project:
- Initialized: {{if .Initialized}}yes ({{.ProjectRoot}}){{else}}no{{end}}
- Daemon: {{.DaemonStatus}}
- Database: {{.DatabaseSize}}

Memory:
- Events captured: {{.TotalEvents}}
- Insights extracted: {{.TotalInsights}}
- Recent activity (last 5 min): {{.RecentEventCount}} events
{{- if .CategoryBreakdown}}
- Categories: {{.CategoryBreakdown}}
{{- end}}

Cognitive mode (if active): {{if .CurrentMode}}{{.CurrentMode}}{{if .ModeDescription}} — {{.ModeDescription}}{{end}}{{else}}idle{{end}}

Summary:
